The ONNX embedder compiles, but the provider fallback path does not cover EP registration/session creation failures, which violates the intended runtime fallback behavior for unavailable providers.

Review comment:

- [P2] Retry CPU when EP registration fails — /home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb-worktrees/0.8.16-slice-10-20260708T192441Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-embedder/src/ort_bge.rs:282-285
  When `FATHOMDB_EMBED_DEVICE` requests CUDA/ROCm/DirectML/OpenVINO and the ORT library reports that EP as compiled in, `resolve_effective_provider` keeps the GPU provider, but `with_execution_providers` can still fail during provider registration/session creation if runtime dependencies or the requested device are unusable. In that common unavailable-provider case this constructor returns an error instead of the documented loud CPU fallback, so users with a CUDA-enabled ORT but missing CUDA/cuDNN libs (or a bad device id) cannot open the embedder at all.
